Sicario is a 2015 American crime drama film directed by Denis Villeneuve , written by Taylor Sheridan , and starring Emily Blunt , Benicio del Toro , and Josh Brolin .
It is about a principled FBI agent who is enlisted by a government task force to bring down the leader of a powerful and brutal Mexican drug cartel .
Sicario was selected to compete for the Palme d'Or at the 2015 Cannes Film Festival .
It began a limited release in the United States on September 18 , 2015 , prior to a nationwide release on October 2 , 2015 .
The film received three Academy Award nominations for Best Cinematography , Best Original Score , and Best Sound Editing , as well as three BAFTA nominations for Best Supporting Actor , Best Cinematography , and Best Film Music .
It was criticized by viewers in Mexico for the depiction of the city of Juarez where part of the plot takes place .
A sequel , Soldado , began shooting in November 2016 .